tip.text: Choc & Peanut butter milkshake is da bomb! Also chicken patties are nicer than the beefs. Route 66 with chicken patty is delish!!
Absolutely delicious chee cheong fun! Make sure u order from the old man in the back as they are two stalls here. It's plain and not warm but it's really good. So famous that it's sold out by 9am!
'Will you berry me' (pancakes with berry compote) for brunch is a dream come true. So satisfying. Happy days!

tip.text: Must pair Nasi Lemak Ayam goreng with milo dinasaur! Roti bakar and roti sambal are good too!
Don't leave without trying the chocolate dream dessert. Fantastic closing but remember to order ahead of time as it takes 20-25 mins to prepare!
Had the tender chicken, asparagus and cold cuts tapas which was all very good. And we all loved the pollo paella (chicken!). Made us love paella all over again! Service a lil slow tho.
Seriously catching us by surprise. The KLonuts are surprisingly good! It's freshly made! Definitely a recommendation to try despite it being small portion!

tip.text: Siu yuk (melts in your mouth), kailan (fried 2 ways) and Hokkien mee were all fantastic and fulfilling. Will come back for the Peking duck next time!
The perfect Italian place. Ordered the recommended fried mozzarella cheese, carbonara and pork belly. All fantastic and filling! Pork belly is as big as an iPhone!

Stuck in a jam so I googled up somewhere nearby and stumbled upon this cute lil neighbourhood! Treating myself to a dinner for one! Chicken mushroom pie is a twist with actually soup under the pastry!

They did my wedding cake and pre cocktail savories. Not only gorgeous and met expectations but the quality and taste was wonderful. Everyone loved it! (Left is original and right pic is what they did)
